               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170219-153-person1144">
                  CHARLES 
                  DOWNER
               <interp inst="t18170219-153-person1144" type="surname" value="DOWNER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170219-153-person1144" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170219-153-person1144" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live with Mr. Needles, who is a <rs id="t18170219-153-viclabel874" type="occupation">pawnbroker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170219-153-victim1143 t18170219-153-viclabel874"></join>. On the 12th of February, the stockings hung by the door. The prisoner and a lad came into the shop to pledge a handkerchief; he went out. There was a looking-glass in the shop; I saw by the reflection, that that the prisoner was taking the stockings. I pursued him; he ran down Gun-street - I lost him. About twenty minutes after, they both passed the shop again - I ran out and secured him. I did not find the stockings on him, but I am positive that I saw him take them.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18170219-153-verdict875" type="verdictDescription">
